Description: A comprehensive toolkit for importing, filtering, analyzing, and visualizing 
    data from MiteMap tracking systems. MiteMap is a Raspberry Pi-based system used to 
    track arthropod movement in 2D arenas, commonly used in behavioral ecology research 
    to study chemotactic responses to volatile compounds. This package provides functions 
    to process raw tracking data, filter movement trajectories, compute behavioral metrics 
    (time spent in different zones, distance traveled, immobility periods), and create 
    publication-ready visualizations including heatmaps, trajectory plots, and statistical 
    summaries. Supports both raw positional data and processed zone-based metrics (HH and 
    CH formats) as described in Masier et al. (2022) <doi:10.1002/jez.2651>. 
